README lists this as intentionally excluded: \"a finalized component import / linking story across generated files\".

When \`<CounterPanel>\` is used in a template, there is no mechanism to resolve it to another \`.mbtv\` file, compile it, and link the generated modules together.

This is the most critical gap for building real applications.

## Needed

- Convention for component resolution (file-based or explicit import)
- Cross-file dependency tracking
- Bundle/module assembly from compiled outputs